Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.71,0:00:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,[Men shouting in spanish]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.67,0:00:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,[Steve] {\i1}Pablo Escobar\Nsaid, "sometimes I'm god.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.13,0:00:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I say a man dies,\Nhe dies the same day."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.39,0:00:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,[Screaming sobs]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.60,0:00:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In his career, this asshole killed\Nthousands of police officers{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.35,0:00:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}at a rate of over 400 a year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.98,0:00:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}With numbers like that staring\Nyou in the face, you have to ask...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.69,0:00:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What possesses a man to put on a uniform{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.90,0:00:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that all but guarantees\Nhis days are numbered?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.70,0:00:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[Shouting in spanish]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.41,0:00:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Most of them were just kids,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.37,0:00:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}raised to reach a fork in the\Nroad and choose the right path.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.50,0:01:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Fight for the good guys.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.17,0:01:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were young, they\Nwere full of hope...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.68,0:01:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And they thought they were invincible.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.85,0:01:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And those that were left\Nbehind would feel their loss the most.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.69,0:01:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Everybody's got a breaking point,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.94,0:01:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when shit sickens them so\Nmuch that they just have to act.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.44,0:01:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For Pinzón, that breaking\Npoint meant resignation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.74,0:01:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[Steve] {\i1}But there were\Nthose who couldn't resign,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.01,0:01:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}who couldn't just walk away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.04,0:01:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Man shouts orders in spanish]\N- {\i1}Presidents have breaking points, too.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.00,0:01:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And Gaviria had finally found his.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.04,0:02:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,[Phone ringing]
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.64,0:02:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,[latin guitar theme music plays]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.15,0:04:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,[Slow Latin song plays]
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[Horse whinnies nearby]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.54,0:08:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- [juan pablo] We're safe!\N- [Man] Pass me the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.00,0:08:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- [juan pablo] Here you go.\N- Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.55,0:08:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,[Chatter continues outside]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.10,0:08:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[gato]
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.18,0:08:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,[Children laughing]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.62,0:09:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,[Helicopter approaching]
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.11,0:09:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,[Indistinct]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.43,0:10:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,[Steve] {\i1}This is Gilberto\NRodriguez Orejuela.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.23,0:10:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And if you've never heard of him,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.86,0:10:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}it's because that's\Nexactly the way he wants it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.23,0:10:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ask him what he does for a living and\Nhe'll tell you that he's a banker,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.78,0:10:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and that would be true.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.40,0:10:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In fact, he and his brother\NMiguel controlled their own bank.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.62,0:10:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or he might tell you that he and\Nhis brother owned and operated{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.62,0:10:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}one of Colombia’s largest\Nchains of drug stores.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The brothers could also tell you they{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.12,0:10:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}ran their own soccer team.\NWhich they did.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.04,0:10:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}América de Cali, one of the\Nbest teams on the continent{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.71,0:10:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and a fierce rival of\NPablo’s Atlético national.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.93,0:10:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But what they'd never tell you is\Nthat these businesses were a front{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.10,0:10:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and that the Rodriguez brothers{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.06,0:10:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}were the second biggest cocaine\Ntraffickers in the world:{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.10,0:11:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The leaders of the Cali cartel.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.19,0:11:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Like Pablo and the Medellín cartel,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.36,0:11:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they started out as\Nrun-of-the-mill criminals: Bank robbers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.03,0:11:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And with all that money they\Nscored from their heists,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.66,0:11:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they quickly graduated\Nto smuggling weed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.28,0:11:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And when they realized\Nthat ten pounds of blow{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.16,0:11:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was worth as much as a ton of marijuana,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.29,0:11:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they jumped headfirst into\Nthe cocaine business.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.29,0:11:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These guys were no piece\Nof shit street dealers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.25,0:11:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They planned meticulously, maximizing\Nprofit, minimizing risk.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.63,0:11:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As the business grew, a\Nyoung ambitious Colombian kid,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.09,0:11:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a guy you might know named Pacho\NHerrera, was such a good earner{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.60,0:11:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that the brothers\Neventually promoted him to partner.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.10,0:11:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But they had a competitor,\Nand not just any competitor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.15,0:11:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}One that wasn't interested in{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.63,0:11:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}abdicating the throne\Nas the king of coke.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.90,0:11:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don Pablo.\N- {\i1}But Gilberto was smart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.95,0:11:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He didn't care that\NEscobar wore the crown.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.07,0:11:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So they went to him with a proposal,\NMiami, the cocaine capital of the world,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.74,0:12:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}would remain Pablo’s territory, and\Nin return, the Rodriguez brothers{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.92,0:12:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}would make do with a little territory\Nin the northeast called new york city.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.50,0:12:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- [Up-tempo dance music plays]\N- The extra 1,089 miles may have made it{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.76,0:12:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a little harder to get to, but\Nit turns out the folks in new york{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.47,0:12:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}were just as head over heels for\Ncocaine as the folks down south.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.56,0:12:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And while there were 1.8\Nmillion people in Miami,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.56,0:12:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}there were seven\Nmillion in new york city.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.73,0:12:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As much as the Cali guys loved\Nmoney and the finer things in life,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.52,0:12:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}they hated the wrong kind of attention.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.69,0:12:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}For the "gentlemen of Cali," it was{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.72,0:12:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}about appearing like\Nlegitimate businessmen.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.28,0:12:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And business was good. But that\Ndidn't mean that it couldn't get better.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.29,0:14:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[Steve] {\i1}This was one thing that the\NCali guys and the DEA could agree on.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.38,0:14:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As controversial as colonel\NCarrillo's methods were,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.72,0:15:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he was the only guy that\NEscobar was afraid of.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.76,0:15:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And returning\Ncommand of search bloc to him{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.89,0:15:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was exactly what we needed.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.18,0:15:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The president has offered us every\Navailable resource to defeat Escobar.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.27,0:15:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,All we have to do now\Nis manage it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.35,0:15:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm still gonna rely\Non intelligence from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.86,0:15:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're gonna do\Nthings a little bit differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.53,0:15:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No more large-scale operations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:22.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Search bloc goes back\Nto small-scale tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.45,0:15:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- Amen.\N- Stealth operations, surprise raids,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.74,0:15:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that sort of thing. We change the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.70,0:15:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's one thing that\Nwe need to do first. Trujillo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.88,0:15:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,A hundred men? That's not\Nexactly small-scale tactics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.80,0:15:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,First thing is, we let\NPablo know that we're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.18,0:15:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[Sirens chirping]
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.35,0:15:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,[Steve] {\i1}Now you can bet that the\Nsecond a convoy of a hundred men{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.65,0:16:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and six marked police\Ntrucks leave that base,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.15,0:16:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}that Escobar's army of spotters would\Nbe burning up the phone lines{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.36,0:16:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}- just to tell Escobar all about it.{\i0}\N- [Phone rings]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.37,0:16:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,[Steve] {\i1}And you'd be\Nright. But that was the point.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.09,0:16:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You see, these spotters made\Nit impossible for us to operate{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.09,0:16:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in the secrecy we required.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.30,0:16:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So we needed to blind them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.39,0:16:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And the first step to blinding someone\Nis getting them to open their eyes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.44,0:16:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably this rooftop here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.60,0:16:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[Steve] {\i1}Once those signals\Nwent up, we could pick them up,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.65,0:16:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}get a fix and get a\Nlocation of each one.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.08,0:16:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,[Men chattering in spanish]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.80,0:17:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,[Man]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.34,0:17:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,[Steve] {\i1}And I guess you could say that\Nthe second part of Carrillo's plan{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.72,0:17:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was to show Pablo that the\Nsheriff was back in town.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.81,0:17:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And he did that the best way he could.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.99,0:18:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.26,0:18:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.83,0:19:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- We got 'em.\N- Keeps going like that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.87,0:19:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,until you reached barrio Pablo Escobar.\NWe captured six radio transmissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.59,0:19:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But we haven't\Npinpointed the exact location.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.46,0:19:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, sir.\N- So our best bet
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.67,0:19:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is to corner each of these\Nbuildings. This time, we hit the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.73,0:19:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Peña, you're with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.57,0:19:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Murphy, Jacoby, you\Nstay here to guide us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.49,0:19:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- Careful out there.\N- [Javier sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.49,0:19:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,[Up-tempo Latin song plays]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.83,0:19:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[Laughing]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.75,0:19:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Indistinct chatter in spanish]\N- [Engines start]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.71,0:19:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- [In spanish]\N- [Weapons cocking]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.35,0:19:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[Man]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.56,0:20:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we got one. Spotter one is down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.99,0:20:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,[Mutters in spanish]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.99,0:20:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,[Man shouts]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.91,0:20:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,-\N- [Man whistles]
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.21,0:20:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Woman chatters in spanish]\N-
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.78,0:21:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,-\N- Shut up, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.68,0:22:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,[Carrillo cocks pistol]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.11,0:22:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,[Carrillo]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.31,0:24:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,[pablo]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.28,0:24:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,[Dishes clattering]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.84,0:24:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,-\N- [Hermilda] Tata.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.50,0:26:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Javi, where are the fucking spotters?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.37,0:26:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Carrillo went a different\Nway. He, uh... he cut them loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.29,0:26:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're letting people go now?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.92,0:26:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Murphy, we're letting people go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.01,0:26:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.72,0:26:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don't worry about it, man.\N- Hey, fucking talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.97,0:26:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- Let go of my fucking arm.\N- What the fuck happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.98,0:27:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Carrillo put a gun to the kid's\Nhead and he pulled the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.69,0:27:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,To make a fucking point.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.78,0:27:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We good now?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.49,0:27:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,[Engine starts]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.66,0:27:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.96,0:27:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,[Up-tempo Latin music playing]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.93,0:27:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[Grunts]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.15,0:27:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,[La Quica sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.87,0:27:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,[Sighs]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.17,0:28:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,[Starts engine]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.39,0:28:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[Knocks on door]
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.68,0:28:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to talk to you about\Nwhat happened tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.19,0:28:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,- What do you think happened?\N- I know I got left behind on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.32,0:28:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,For your own best interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.82,0:28:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know a goddamn\Nthing about my best interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.78,0:28:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Murphy, what happens out\Nthere isn't really for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.20,0:28:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- But it is for Peña?\N- You're not Peña.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.08,0:28:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- 'Cause I'm a damn gringo.\N- Because I trust him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.25,0:28:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you try me?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.96,0:28:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This fight against\NEscobar, you want to win it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.58,0:28:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,These guys aren't fighting by\Nthe same rules, so why should we?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.84,0:28:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- You know what that means?\N- Oh, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.68,0:29:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether this is about protecting\Nme or protecting you, stop icing me out.
